ell with 与…很搭","headword":"go well with"},{"type":"entry","text":"dot [dɒt]","headword":"dot"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.点，小圆点"},{"type":"note","text":"◎on the dot准时地"},{"type":"entry","text":"necessary element 必需元素","headword":"necessary element"},{"type":"entry","text":"classical collocation 经典搭配","headword":"classical collocation"}]},{"number":429,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"originate in 起源于","headword":"originate in"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"text","text":"有趣的小词belt"},{"type":"entry","text":"Below the belt原意是“拳击手腰带以下部位（击此部位为犯规行","headword":"Below the belt"},{"type":"text","text":"为）”，后来引申为“暗中伤人，不择手段，用不正当手段攻击”。比如"},{"type":"text","text":"有人运用不正当手段或卑鄙手法做事，你可提醒他（她）：That's"},{"type":"text","text":"below the belt。"}]}]}